.TH IDLE 1
.SH NAME
idle \- detect when the user is not idle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B o/idle
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Idle
updates
.BI /mnt/who/ user /last
with
.B $sysname
whenever it thinks the user started to use the machine by
looking at mouse/keyboard activity and to the status of the
screen saver.
.SH SOURCE
.B /usr/octopus/MacOSX/idle.b
.br
.B /usr/octopus/Plan9/idle.b
.SH BUGS
The Plan 9 version only works for Plan B kernels.

